==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: amphotericin B
<hw>amphotericin B</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>an antibiotic and antifungal agent
(<chform>C47H73NO17</chform>), produced by a strain of
<prodby><spn>Streptomyces nodosus</spn></prodby>. It is one of a class
of polyene macrolide antibiotics effective against fungal infections. It
has a molecular weight of 924.11; it is soluble in organic solvents but
only slightly soluble in water.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Fungizone.</syn>
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>ampicillin</ent>⟦br⟧
